def: Of or pertaining to the peritoneum.
To be too trustful or confident; to trust too much. [Obs.]Wyclif
The place or space beneath the surface of the ground;subterranean space.A spirit raised from depth of underground. Shak.
Belonging to, or resembling, the perches, or family Percidæ.-- n.
A borosilicate of iron and lime, near datolite in form andcomposition.
Pertaining to baptism; as, baptismal vows. Baptismal name, theChristian name, which is given at baptism.
Having the nose broad; -- opposed to Ant: leptorhine.-- n. (Zoöl.)
